The second season of Yakusoku no Neverland. Fifteen children escape Grace Field House, a false paradise, hoping for a chance at freedom. Instead, they encounter plants and animals they have never before seen, and are chased by demons. The outside world is so beautiful, and yet is almost too cruel to face. Even so, the children refuse to give up. They are guided in their search for better lives only by a message from Minerva and a pen Norman left behind in order to fulfill their promise to return to the House to save those of their family who are still trapped within.
(Source: Aniplex of America) Note: Episode 1 streamed early on Amazon Prime on Jan 7, 2021. The regular TV broadcast started on Jan 8, 2021.
Tsuihou Sareta Onimotsu Tamer, Sekai Yuiitsu no Necromancer ni Kakusei Suru: The Tale of the Necromancer.

Recon, mapping, carrying baggage, cooking, keeping watch, taking blows… even while doing all these things, the tamer, Randall, is called a burden and useless by his party members.
This S-ranked party is filled with genius magicians, excellent swordsmen, famous priests, and great knights, that show superb teamwork and drive, which helped them become the most famous party in the country.
But despite being incredibly popular, the members of the party feel dissatisfied with Randall. He soon gets kicked out just while he was gaining influence of his own and unlocks his true power while seeking for his revenge.

In a world where technology and magic are almost indistinguishable from one another, monsters and creatures of myth and legend reign terror upon mankind. In humanity’s darkest moment, individuals with special god-like powers emerge to save the day. They are — the Awakened. Meet Jae-Hyun, a feeble Awakened human Raider, who struggles to make ends meet until one day a series of confounding events allow him to claim a powerful item that will change the course of history forever… (Source: WEBTOONS, edited)
